<subSubSection id="C36918B3FFDEFF91FCF3F91CFBBCC8FF" pageId="18" pageNumber="43" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BCC4B38FFDEFF91FCF3F91CFB32C99D" blockId="18.[813,1457,1740,1791]" pageId="18" pageNumber="43">ETYMOLOGY. — The specific epithet refers to the short scape (or sexually reproductive stem) of the species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC4B38FFDEFF91FCF3F8CAFBBCC8FF" blockId="18.[811,1457,1819,1948]" pageId="18" pageNumber="43">
HABITAT AND PHENOLOGY. — Primary and secondary dry evergreen broad-leaved forests on eroded marble-like crystalline limestone at elevations 
<quantity id="4C8BE6DDFFDEFF91FC4AF89EFBF5C804" box="[916,1027,1871,1895]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="18" pageNumber="43" unit="m" value="175.0" valueMax="200.0" valueMin="150.0">150-200 m</quantity>
a.s.l. Obligate lithophyte on shady vertical limestone cliffs. Flowers in September-October. Rare. Expected IUCN Red List status – DD.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36918B3FFDEFF90FCF3F868FE40CE12" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="18" pageNumber="43" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BCC4B38FFDEFF91FCF3F868FB9CC889" blockId="18.[811,1456,1976,2027]" pageId="18" pageNumber="43">
DISTRIBUTION. — 
<emphasis id="B907972AFFDEFF91FC3EF869FBF8C8B3" bold="true" box="[992,1038,1976,2000]" pageId="18" pageNumber="43">
<collectingCountry id="F3640BA8FFDEFF91FC3EF869FBF8C8B3" box="[992,1038,1976,2000]" name="Laos" pageId="18" pageNumber="43">Laos</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
(
<collectingRegion id="49B785DAFFDEFF91FBC7F869FB08C8B3" box="[1049,1278,1976,2000]" country="Laos" name="Khammouan" pageId="18" pageNumber="43">Khammouane province</collectingRegion>
, Thakhek district). Local endemic of southern Laos.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC4B38FFDFFF90FF5AFF08FF01CF93" blockId="19.[132,775,217,369]" box="[132,247,217,243]" pageId="19" pageNumber="44">AFFINITIES</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC4B38FFDFFF90FF5AFF26FE40CE12" blockId="19.[132,775,217,369]" pageId="19" pageNumber="44">
This new species is allied to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7330BBFFDFFF90FE7EFF29FCF6CE72" authority="Aver. &amp; N. Tanaka" authorityName="Aver. &amp; N. Tanaka" box="[416,768,247,273]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Tupistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="theana">
<emphasis id="B907972AFFDFFF90FE7EFF29FDCACE72" box="[416,572,247,273]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="44">Tupistra theana</emphasis>
Aver.&amp; N.Tanaka
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from it by the much shorter peduncle, fewer flowers per scape, outer floral bracts exceeding the flowers, and the smaller tripartite stigma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36918B3FFDFFF90FF5AFE46FD4FC86F" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCC4B38FFDFFF90FF5AFE46FEE3CECC" blockId="19.[130,777,407,1804]" box="[132,277,407,433]" pageId="19" pageNumber="44">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC4B38FFDFFF90FF5AFE67FD4FC86F" blockId="19.[130,777,407,1804]" pageId="19" pageNumber="44">
Lithophytic perennial herb. Rhizome erect or suberect, simple or a few branched, terete, stout, slightly woody, dark browngray to almost black, 5-10(15) cm long, (1.2)1.5-2(2.2) cm in diam. Roots cord-like, thick, fleshy, covered densely with black root hairs in most part. Stem erect, very short, 
<quantity id="4C8BE6DDFFDFFF90FD79FDE7FCF1CD32" box="[679,775,566,593]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" unit="cm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1-1.5 cm</quantity>
tall, covered with dilated leaf bases and fibrous remnants of decaying sheath leaves (cataphylls). Sheath leaves straight or slightly recurved, ensiform, conduplicate, green, (3.5)5-15(20) cm long, (0.4)0.6-1(1.4) cm wide, fugacious, becoming soon drying, papyraceous and dull yellowish-brown. Leaves basal, (2)3-5(6), suberect to arcuate, sub-sessile, equitant, indistinctly petiolate, oblanceolate, (0.7)0.9-1.3(1.5) m long, (3.5)4-5(6) cm wide, gradually tapering to rigid, canaliculate, petiole-like base, acute at apex, rigid, leathery, uniformly green, glossy, midvein prominent abaxially. Peduncle arising from top of stem, axillary, erect, straight, rigid, 4-6(8) cm long, (1.5) 
<quantity id="4C8BE6DDFFDFFF90FD2CFC44FF32CCAC" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2- 3 mm</quantity>
in diam., naked, fleshy, white to light green, becoming slightly thicker upward. Inflorescence a simple, loose, terminal spadix-like spike of several flowers, 2.5-3(4.5) cm long, 
<quantity id="4C8BE6DDFFDFFF90FD05FC24FF39CB4C" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" unit="cm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.2">1.2- 1.5 cm</quantity>
in diam.; rachis several-angled longitudinally, fleshy, slightly raised around flower pits. Floral bracts 2 per flower, triangular, conduplicate toward base, spreading, becoming drying, papyraceous, dull yellowish-brown to dark brown; outer bract located below flower, acute to acuminate, finely serrulate distally, (6)8-12(14) mm long, (5)6-8(9) mm wide, exceeding the flower; inner bract (bracteole) lying lateral to flower, acute, oblique, (3.5)4-6(7) mm long, 1.5-2(2.5) mm wide. Flowers several, sessile, campanulate or suburceolate, not fully open, 
<quantity id="4C8BE6DDFFDFFF90FEFAFAE2FE8CCA2D" box="[292,378,1331,1358]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">6-8 mm</quantity>
across; perianth (7)8-9(10) mm long, 6-cleft distally, cup or bowl-shaped in proximal half, dark dirty purple, fleshy; segments triangular-ovate, obtuse and often irregularly serrulate apically, 
<quantity id="4C8BE6DDFFDFFF90FE41FA42FDFFCACD" box="[415,521,1427,1454]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.75" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="4.75" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.5">4.5-5 mm</quantity>
long and wide. Stamens 6, opposite to perianth segments; anthers inserted at perianth tube close to base of segments, ellipsoid, introrse, slightly incurved, 1.5-1.8(2) mm long, light dull yellow, dorsifixed on short fleshy filaments 
<quantity id="4C8BE6DDFFDFFF90FE51F9C3FE15C94E" box="[399,483,1554,1581]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
long. Ovaryexternally very indistinct, 3-loculed, each locule with 1 lens-shaped ovule on an axial placenta; style columnar, slightly broadened toward the base, truncate at apex, 3-ridged longitudinally, yellowishpink, 
<quantity id="4C8BE6DDFFDFFF90FF1AF943FEF2C9CE" box="[196,260,1682,1709]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
tall, 
<quantity id="4C8BE6DDFFDFFF90FEE4F943FE51C9CE" box="[314,423,1682,1709]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1-1.5 mm</quantity>
in diam., not exceeding the base of anthers; stigma 3-partite, 
<quantity id="4C8BE6DDFFDFFF90FE6AF963FDD6C9AE" box="[436,544,1714,1741]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="1.1" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="1.0">1-1.2 mm</quantity>
in diam., almost dull yellowish-brown, lobes rectangular, convex,ventrally grooved longitudinally, densely papillulate. Fruits unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36918B3FFDFFF90FF5AF8E3FACCCDF3" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCC4B38FFDFFF90FF5AF8E3FF1EC829" blockId="19.[131,776,1842,2028]" box="[132,232,1842,1868]" pageId="19" pageNumber="44">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC4B38FFDFFF90FF5AF883FBDFCE11" blockId="19.[131,776,1842,2028]" lastBlockId="19.[811,1457,215,656]" pageId="19" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicName id="4C7330BBFFDFFF90FF5AF883FDE7C808" authority="Aver. &amp; N.Tanaka" authorityName="Aver. &amp; N. Tanaka" authorityYear="2015" box="[132,529,1873,1900]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Tupistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="breviscapa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B907972AFFDFFF90FF5AF883FEBEC808" box="[132,328,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="44">Tupistra breviscapa</emphasis>
Aver. &amp; N.Tanaka
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2342A51FFDFFF90FDC5F883FD9AC80F" box="[539,620,1874,1900]" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is most closely allied to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7330BBFFDFFF90FF3AF8A3FDE2C8E8" authority="Aver. &amp; N. Tanaka" authorityName="Aver. &amp; N. Tanaka" box="[228,532,1905,1932]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Tupistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="theana">
<emphasis id="B907972AFFDFFF90FF3AF8A3FEB1C8E8" box="[228,327,1905,1931]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="44">T. theana</emphasis>
Aver. &amp; N.Tanaka
</taxonomicName>
from central 
<collectingCountry id="F3640BA8FFDFFF90FD77F8A0FCF1C8E8" box="[681,775,1905,1931]" name="Vietnam" pageId="19" pageNumber="44">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE236C9FFDFFF90FF52F840FE5BC8C8" author="AVERYANOV L. V. &amp; TANAKA N." box="[140,429,1937,1963]" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" pagination="153 - 167" refId="ref12952" refString="AVERYANOV L. V. &amp; TANAKA N. 2012. - New species of Peliosanthes and Tupistra (Asparagaceae) from eastern Indochina. Taiwania 57: 153 - 167." type="journal article" year="2012">Averyanov &amp; Tanaka 2012</bibRefCitation>
) in having a similar floral shape, similar coloration of perianth and style, and a relatively small pistil. It differs, however, by the much shorter peduncle (vs peduncle over 
<quantity id="4C8BE6DDFFDFFF90FC10FF06FBE1CF91" box="[974,1047,215,242]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" unit="cm" value="20.0">20 cm</quantity>
), fewer flowers per scape, outer floral bracts exceeding the flowers (vs bracts as long as the flowers), and the smaller tripartite stigma nearly as broad as the style (vs indistinctly 3-lobed or nearly entire stigma significantly broader than the style).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC4B38FFDFFF90FC9DFEA6FACCCDF3" blockId="19.[811,1457,215,656]" pageId="19" pageNumber="44">
The new species appears close to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C7330BBFFDFFF90FAC3FEA6FA9FCEF2" authorityName="Kabata" authorityYear="1992" box="[1309,1385,375,401]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Rohdea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907972AFFDFFF90FAC3FEA6FA9FCEF2" box="[1309,1385,375,401]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="44">Rohdea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE236C9FFDFFF90FAA9FEA6FC9CCED2" author="ROTH A. W." pageId="19" pageNumber="44" refId="ref13563" refString="ROTH A. W. 1821. - Rohdea. Novae Plantarum Species praesertim Indiae orientalis: 196." type="book" year="1821">Roth 1821</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE236C9FFDFFF90FCA9FE47FBEFCED2" author="TANAKA N." box="[887,1049,406,433]" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" pagination="329 - 333" refId="ref13783" refString="TANAKA N. 2003 a. - New combinations in Rohdea (Convallariaceae). Novon 13: 329 - 333." type="journal article" year="2003">Tanaka 2003a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE236C9FFDFFF90FBF9FE46FB98CED2" author="TANAKA N." box="[1063,1134,407,433]" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref13882" refString="TANAKA N. 2010 a. - A taxonomic revision of the genus Rohdea (Asparagaceae). Makinoa New Series 9: 1 - 54." type="book chapter" year="2010">2010a</bibRefCitation>
) in having a relatively small tripartite stigma, but is assignable to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7330BBFFDFFF90FB14FE66FAD6CEB3" box="[1226,1312,439,464]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Tupistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907972AFFDFFF90FB14FE66FAD6CEB3" box="[1226,1312,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="44">Tupistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE236C9FFDFFF90FAF1FE66FC9FCE93" author="KER GAWLER J. B." pageId="19" pageNumber="44" refId="ref13367" refString="KER GAWLER J. B. 1814. - Tupistra. Botanical Magazine 40: pl. 1655." type="book" year="1814">Ker Gawler 1814</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE236C9FFDFFF90FCACFE07FBFBCE93" author="TANAKA N." box="[882,1037,470,496]" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" pagination="334 - 336" refId="ref13805" refString="TANAKA N. 2003 b. - Inclusion of Tricalistra and Gonioscypha muricata in Tupistra (Convallariaceae). Novon 13: 334 - 336." type="journal article" year="2003">Tanaka 2003b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE236C9FFDFFF90FBC6FE07FBA9CE92" author="TANAKA N." box="[1048,1119,470,497]" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" pagination="55 - 93" refId="ref13909" refString="TANAKA N. 2010 b. - A taxonomic revision of the genus Tupistra (Asparagaceae). Makinoa New Series 9: 55 - 93." type="book chapter" year="2010">2010b</bibRefCitation>
) by the leaf with a more slender petiole-like base, purplish perianth (vs greenish perianth), and the stout style nearly as thick as the ovary. Of the species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7330BBFFDFFF90FCF3FDE6FC74CD33" box="[813,898,567,592]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Tupistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907972AFFDFFF90FCF3FDE6FC74CD33" box="[813,898,567,592]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="44">Tupistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
hitherto known, the new species seems to retain the most primitive character state especially as to pistil. In this respect, it may be more primitive than 
<taxonomicName id="4C7330BBFFDFFF90FB0FFDA6FAC5CDF3" box="[1233,1331,630,656]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Tupistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="theana">
<emphasis id="B907972AFFDFFF90FB0FFDA6FAC5CDF3" box="[1233,1331,630,656]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="44">T. theana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
